I'll start by writing the Architecture Decision Record (ADR) to document the design before implementing.  [33m> Write[0m(file_path='docs/adrs/ADR-076-double-agent-tdd-flow.md', content="# ADR-076: Double-Agent TDD Flow\n\n## Status\n\n**Accepted**\n\n## Context\n\nD.U.H. currently supports single-agent execution and multi-agent collaboration via `Agent` and `Swarm` tools. However, it lacks a structured **Test-Driven Development (TDD)** flow that enforces the **red-green-refactor** cycle with distinct **Driver** and **Navigator** roles.\n\nThe TDD cycle is a proven methodology in software development that improves code quality, test coverage, and design clarity. Implementing this as a first-class feature in D.U.H. would:\n- Enforce discipline in test writing before implementation\n- Provide clear separation of concerns between test design and implementation\n- Enable collaborative review and refactoring between agents\n- Improve reliability of changes by validating each step\n\n## Decision\n\nWe will implement a **double-agent TDD flow** as a new **PlanMode** in D.U.H. The flow will:\n\n1. Use two cooperating agents:\n   - **Driver**: Writes the failing test (RED), then writes the minimum code to make it pass (GREEN), then refactors\n   - **Navigator**: Reviews the test spec before RED, suggests refac
