  [33m> Now I'll create a wiki page for the TDD flow.[0m(file_path='docs/wiki/TDD-Flow.md', content='# Double-Agent TDD Flow\n\nD.U.H. implements a **double-agent Test-Driven Development (TDD)** flow using the red-green-refactor method with distinct **Driver** and **Navigator** roles. This feature enforces discipline in test writing and provides collaborative review between agents.\n\n## Overview\n\nThe TDD flow proceeds through six phases in strict order:\n\n1. **Navigator drafts the test spec**\n2. **Driver writes the failing test (RED)** — must fail, else Navigator revises spec\n3. **Driver writes the minimum code to pass (GREEN)**\n4. **Navigator proposes a refactor**\n5. **Driver applies the refactor**\n6. **Navigator validates tests still pass and refactor landed cleanly**\n\n## Roles\n\n| Role | Responsibility | Model Tier | Agent Type |\n|------|----------------|------------|------------|\n| **Driver** | Writes tests and implementation code | medium | coder |\n| **Navigator** | Reviews specs, proposes refactors, validates | large | reviewer |\n\n## Usage\n\n### CLI Flag\n\n```bash\nduh --plan-mode tdd -p "Add a new feature to auth module"\n```\n\n### REPL Slash Command\n\n```\n/plan tdd Add a new feature to auth module\n```\n\n## Example Workflow\n\n```bash\n$ duh --plan-mode tdd -p "Add rate limiting to the API"\n\nTDD Phase: Spec Draft\nNavigator drafting test spec\n\nTDD Phase: Red\nDriver writing failing test\n\n> Edit(file="tests/test_api.py", ...)\n  ✓ Applied edit to tests/test_api.py\n\n=== FAIL: test_api.py::TestAPI::test_rate_limiting\nAssertionError: Expected 429 status code for too many requests\n\nTDD Phase: Green\nDriver writing minimum code to pass\n\n> Edit(file="api.py", ...)\n  ✓ Applied edit to api.py\n\n=== 1 passed in 0.12s\n\nTDD Phase: Refactor Propose\nNavigator proposing refactor\n\nRefactor Plan:\n- Extract rate limiting logic to separate module\n- Add configuration for rate limit thresholds\n\nTDD Phase: Refactor Apply\nDriver applying refactor\n\n> Edit(file="api.py", ...)\n> Edit(file="rate_limiter.py", ...)\n  ✓ Applied edits to api.py and rate_limiter.py\n\nTDD Phase: Validate\nNavigator validating refactor\n\n=== 1 passed in 0.14s\nValidation: All tests pass. Refactor applied correctly.\n\n✓ TDD flow completed successfully!\n```\n\n## Error Handling\n\n- **Test passes unexpectedly in RED phase**: Navigator revises the test specification to ensure it will fail initially.\n- **Test fails in GREEN phase**: Driver makes additional implementation attempts.\n- **Validation fails after refactor**: Navigator proposes a corrected refactor plan.\n\n## Configuration\n\nThe TDD flow uses:\n- **Driver**: medium model tier (balanced capability)\n- **Navigator**: large model tier (stronger reasoning)\n\nModel tiers are resolved per-provider:\n\n| Provider | Driver (medium) | Navigator (large) |\n|----------|------------------|--------------------|\n| Anthropic | claude-sonnet-4-6 | claude-opus-4-6 |\n| OpenAI | gpt-4o | o1 |\n| Gemini | gemini-2.5-pro | gemini-3.1-pro-preview |\n| Groq | llama-3.3-70b-versatile | openai/gpt-oss-120b |\n\n## Integration\n\nThe TDD flow integrates with existing D.U.H. features:\n\n- **Tools**: Uses `Edit`, `Bash`, `Swarm`, and `Task` tools\n- **Plan Mode**: Extends the existing plan mode infrastructure\n- **Multi-agent**: Uses `SwarmTool` for parallel agent execution\n- **Error Handling**: Provides clear error messages and retry logic\n\n## Best Practices\n\n1. **Be specific in test specs**: Clearly define what should fail in the RED phase\n2. **Write minimal implementation**: Only implement what\'s needed to pass the test\n3. **Focus refactors on quality**: Improve readability, maintainability, and design\n4. **Validate thoroughly**: Ensure refactors don\'t break existing functionality\n\n## See Also\n\n- [ADR-076: Double-Agent TDD Flow](../../adrs/ADR-076-double-agent-tdd-flow.md)\n- [Multi-Agent Documentation](Multi-Agent.md)\n- [Plan Mode Documentation](Plan-Mode.md)')
